The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 01 July is 44,630 (5,143.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 26 June, there were 820 new confirmed cases (94.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 19 June, there were 494 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 66% (326 extra cases).
